Then `if signer is None: print ... 'Please install...'`

I'd rather not force the pytest runner to make this work. We can use the builtin [unittest `skipUnless`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/unittest.html#unittest.skipUnless) to achieve what we want like so:

```python
from xbee.tornado import has_tornado

@unittest.skipUnless(has_tornado)
class TestReadFromDevice(AsyncTestCase):
```

Did you check that it was broken before? Theses tests look like they would work without any modifications. What you really want to check is 

1. With `strict=True` it throws exception from pre/post_* callbacks (that's how it worked before);
2. (more importantly) Without `strict=False` it does not raise exceptions BUT returns those errors as `errors` field in Marshmal/Unmarshal result.

I believe you can remove the second test if you do this:

```python
@requires_scipy
@pytest.mark.parametrize('method,atol', [('brentq', 1e-11), ('newton', 1e-8)])
def test_v_from_i_methods(fixture_v_from_i, method, atol):
# remove atol spec and set method=method
```

